.SH NAME
\fBplscolbga\fP - Set the background color by 8-bit RGB value and PLFLT alpha transparency value.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBplscolbga\fP(\fIr\fP, \fIg\fP, \fIb\fP, \fIalpha\fP)
.SH DESCRIPTION

.P
Set the background color (color 0 in cmap0) by 8-bit RGB value and PLFLT alpha transparency value (see the PLplot documentation).
.P
This function is used in example 31.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIr\fP (\fBPLINT\fP(3plplot), input)
Unsigned 8-bit integer (0-255) representing the degree of red in the color.
.TP
\fIg\fP (\fBPLINT\fP(3plplot), input)
Unsigned 8-bit integer (0-255) representing the degree of green in the color.
.TP
\fIb\fP (\fBPLINT\fP(3plplot), input)
Unsigned 8-bit integer (0-255) representing the degree of blue in the color.
.TP
\fIalpha\fP (\fBPLFLT\fP(3plplot), input)
Value of the alpha transparency in the range (0.0-1.0).

